Safety
ChessKid is 100% committed to safety!
ChessKid is a safe and friendly site where kids can learn and play chess.
We are committed to ensuring every child using ChessKid has fun and is protected!
Interacting with Members
We do our best to make
ChessKid a safe place for anyone to come and enjoy chess.
We use strict privacy management tools on the site to make sure that kids have safe interactions while using our service. Kid accounts can only send messages to their parent or guardian, and vice versa. Any other communications from kids are limited to a set of pre-determined text options.
No Foul Play or Computer Help
Members can
NEVER use chess programs
(Stockfish, Chess.com Analysis, etc) to analyze any current, ongoing games.
Only One Account
Members may only have one ChessKid account. Members who create more than one account may have all accounts closed.
Please read this entire page for all rules, terms, policies, and agreements on ChessKid!
Privacy Policy
This document describes how we handle your personal information when you use ChessKid.com including our website, mobile and web apps, features, and other services (collectively, the "Services"). By using our Services, you're saying that you have read, understood, and agree to this privacy policy (the "Policy").
We have crafted this Policy with clarity and simplicity in mind, ensuring it is straightforward and easy to understand for everyone.
The Services are brought to you by Chess.com, LLC, the parent company of ChessKid.
We are committed to protecting your privacy and providing you with the best possible experience.
Information We Collect and How We Use It
1. 1.
At ChessKid, we collect minimal personal information from you. This may include information you voluntarily provide, information required for registration, or information collected by us or our service providers.As applicable, we have listed below the legal basis on which we rely to process your personal information.
1. 2.
If you use our Services without registering, we only collect the minimum necessary information to provide the Services (in our legitimate interests to run a successful business), such as your:
IP address
country
timezone
language
page interactions
referrer information, such as the webpage you were on before you landed on our Service
timestamps
information about operating system, device, and browser you are using.
1. 3.
If you create an account, the personal information we collect will depend on if you are a kid or an adult.
1. 4.
In the case of kid accounts, there are three types of accounts, a basic free account, a Gold account, and a student account.
In the case of a basic kid account, we only require you to choose one of the auto-generated usernames and provide us with your parent or legal guardian's email address so we can ask for their permission and keep them informed about your activity (in our legitimate interests to run a safe and kid-friendly Service).
1. 5.
Note that usernames do not use any personal information in the auto-generation process itself and we will not require a kid to provide more information than is reasonably necessary to use the Services or participate in an online activity.
1. 6.
Gold accounts. Gold members have access to additional features such as the ability to customize their username, add their name and last name to their profile, and use the classroom feature. For that reason, if you are a gold member, apart from the basic information, we may also process other information you provide to us which will depend on the gold feature you use. For example, if you use the classroom feature we will process your image and voice provided you enable your deviceÂ´s camera and microphone (we do not keep a record of the classroom session and the camera and microphone are disabled by default). We will process such information in our legitimate interests to run a successful and innovative business.
Other information we may process from gold members is any personal information you choose to include in the customized username (optional), first and last name (optional), school name in case of a student account, email address (optional), and payment and shipping information, when applicable (in our legitimate interest to provide you with information and materials you request from us, and to run our business effectively).
We strongly advise gold members never to provide any personal information in their usernames.
1. 7.
Student Accounts. In some countries, the law permits educational institutions to provide consent on behalf of students' parents, enabling us to lawfully process the necessary information to deliver our Services. For these student accounts, once we have obtained the required consent, we collect the same personal information as we do from our gold members. We also gather any additional personal information provided by the student's teacher or educational institution.
1. 8.
Adult accounts. If you create an adult account, apart from the information listed in point 1.2 we only require you to choose one of the auto-generated usernames and your email address. You will be able to request a custom username which will need to be reviewed and approved by our staff. This information is essential to provide you with the Services. You will also have the ability to associate your account with a kid's or student's account so that you can see their progress at chess, such as the number of games played. If you are an adult and we process personal information about you as described here, we rely on our contractual necessity to provide you with the Services and our legitimate interest to provide you with information and materials you request from us.
1. 9.
After registering, adults will be able to add their name and last name and any other information they would voluntarily want to add to their profile. This information can be edited at any time. We process this information in our legitimate interest to provide the Services to you and to run our business effectively.
1. 10.
Cookies and Tracking Technologies. Cookies and/or similar tracking technologies (collectively referred to as "Cookies") are small pieces of data stored on your device (computer or mobile device). We only use Cookies to provide you with the Services and to enhance your experience on ChessKid. Cookies collect your IP address, country, timezone, device, and browser information and are used because they are essential or because they help us improve your experience. For example, Cookies are used to remember your preferences and login name. We do not use personal information for advertising purposes.
1. 11.
We use the following Cookies to provide our Services:
Strictly Necessary Cookies. These cookies are essential to provide the Services. For example, they allow you to log in to our Services and help the content of pages you request load quickly. Without these Cookies, the Services that you have asked for cannot be provided, and we only use these Cookies to provide you with those Services.
Analytics Cookies. These Cookies are used to collect information about traffic to our Services and how you use our Services. It includes the number of visitors to our Services, the websites that referred them to our Services, the pages they visited on our Services, what time of day they visited our Services, whether they have visited our Services before, and other similar information. We use this information to help operate our Services more efficiently, to gather broad demographic information, and to monitor the level of activity on our Services.
If you are located in the European Economic Area ("EEA") or the UK, you may allow or reject the use of non-Strictly Necessary Cookies when using our Services by changing your Cookie preferences
