1. 12.
Other information.
We will also collect any information you voluntarily provide to us when you contact us directly in our legitimate interests to communicate with you and run an efficient and successful Service.
If we have a contest or sweepstake, we will only ask for more information if we need to.
If a kid participates in the ChessKid Ambassador Program, additional personal information may be requested by us only to the extent necessary.
1. 13.
We provide the option for users to register and sign in using Single Sign-On (SSO) services from third-party providers such as Google and Apple. This feature is entirely optional and offered as an alternative method for user authentication. When you choose to use SSO services, we collect limited information from these third-party providers, used solely for the purpose of creating your account with us and authenticating you. Should you wish to discontinue using SSO at any time, you have the ability to unlink your SSO account from our service through your account settings. This action does not affect the other information associated with your account with us.
How We Share Your Information
2. 1.
We only share your information with others when we need to in order to provide our Services, to make them better, or if the law or government says we have to. We might also share your information with others as detailed in this policy. Where applicable, we have listed below the legal basis on which we rely to process your personal information.
2. 2.
We share your information with some companies that help us run our Services. This includes companies that host our website, process payments, and analyze how our services are used. For example, if you make a payment, we only collect the information needed for that payment (like your credit card number and address) and share it with companies that help make sure the payment goes through safely. Also, if you're an adult and you sign up for our email newsletter or marketing emails, we'll share your email address with the company that helps us send the emails out. We share such information in our legitimate interests to run a successful business.
2. 3.
We also work with companies that help us understand how you and others use our Services. They look at things like how many people visit our Services, what websites sent them to us, which parts of our Services they look at, what time they visit, and if they've been here before. We share this information in our legitimate interests to make our Services work better and to keep track of how busy our Services are. We use Google Analytics, if you want to know how Google uses information from sites or apps, check it out here:
https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites
.
2. 4.
We share your personal information to comply with the law.
We might share your information if the law tells us we have to, or if we really need to in order to follow legal rules or in our legitimate interests to protect our rights, our property, or our safety. We also give information when we respond to legal demands like subpoenas or court orders, or in our legitimate interests to protect our legal rights or defend ourselves against legal claims.
We believe it is necessary to share information in order to investigate, prevent, or take action regarding illegal activities, suspected fraud, situations involving potential threats to the physical safety of any person, violations of ChessKid.com's terms of use, or as otherwise required by law.
2. 5.
Business Transfers: If ChessKid merges with another company, gets bought by someone else, or sells part of its business, your information might be shared during these deals in our legitimate interests to ensure the continuity of our business. We will make sure it's kept private by using confidentiality agreements.
2. 6.
We do not rent or sell your personal information to other people or companies.
2. 7.
To achieve the purposes mentioned in this Policy and to the extent necessary, we may disclose your personal information to affiliates and companies within the Chess.com Group in our legitimate interests to effectively communicate and coordinate within the Chess.com Group.
