Communications With Other Users
4. 1.
Some of the games and activities on our Services let users talk to each other. To keep kids safe and stop them from sharing personal information, messages are very limited. Kids can only start chats with their parents or legal guardians. When playing chess with other users, children can only send pre-selected messages and emojis like "Good luck", "Good game", etc. Kids cannot write their own messages.
4. 2.
Live Classroom. Users are not required to activate their cameras or microphones to participate in a classroom session. However, if you opt to enable these features, please be aware that your image, voice, and physical environment may be incidentally captured and seen by other participants during the classroom session. Any other information voluntarily provided by the user during the session will also be shared. We do not retain any of this information post-session.
Retention of Data
5. 1.
We will keep your personal information only as long as we need it for the reasons explained in this Policy. We will hold onto your information if it's necessary to meet legal requirements (like if laws say we have to keep your data), solve any disputes, and uphold our agreements and policies. We will also keep your information until you tell us not to, in a way that respects your rights and our legal duties.
5. 2.
We might also keep personal information that has been anonymized for our internal analysis. Generally, we keep usage data for a short time, unless we need it to boost security or enhance our Service's functionality, or if the law requires us to keep this data for longer.
Special Note to Parents & School Representatives
6. 1.
At ChessKid, we prioritize the privacy and safety of our young users. We collect the minimal amount of information necessary from children to ensure a functional, engaging, and secure experience on our platforms. To further protect children, our services include features that limit their ability to communicate directly with others. We have designed these measures to prevent the unnecessary disclosure of personal information and to maintain a safe online environment. We are committed to upholding these principles, providing both an educational and safe online experience.
6. 2.
In our commitment to safeguarding the privacy of children and complying with applicable regulations, we make reasonable efforts, in accordance with available technology, to obtain informed consent from parents or legal guardians before processing personal information from Kid accounts.
6. 3.
In some jurisdictions, educational institutions are authorized to consent to the collection of student's information on behalf of the students' parents or legal guardians. This capability allows schools to act as the parent's agent, strictly within the limits established by applicable law. The authority granted to schools is, in general, confined to scenarios that directly pertain to educational functions.
6. 4.
The Internet offers a world of opportunity for children. Your guidance and involvement are essential to help ensure that children have a safe and rewarding online experience. Your efforts to instill responsible information practices will help steer your children to age-appropriate sites and will go a long way toward ensuring that your children have enriching experiences online.
