For purposes of these Terms, "you" and "your" means you as the user of the Services. If you are under the legal age of majority in your jurisdiction or state of residence, before using the services, your parent or legal guardian must read and consent to the ChessKid terms and agree to be responsible for your activities on the Services.
When you use ChessKid you are agreeing to our rules. These Terms are for all ChessKid platforms, whether it's our website, apps, or anything else we create later on. Sometimes, we offer different services that have their own rules. If you use those, make sure to check out their specific terms too as they will apply in addition to these Terms.
This document contains legal terms that may be complex; however, we have made every effort to craft it with clarity and simplicity in mind, ensuring it is straightforward and easy to understand for everyone.
Services
The ChessKid Service is provided as-is, which means ChessKid doesn't promise it will be perfect. ChessKid reserves the right at any time and from time to time to modify or discontinue, temporarily or permanently, the Service (or any part thereof), by providing you with at least 30 days' notice, for example by email or by other means of notification. In limited instances, we may also discontinue the Service without providing notice, as explained in the 'Termination' section below. If at any time you no longer want to use our Service, you are able to delete your account. You agree that ChessKid shall not be liable to you or to any third party for any modification, suspension or discontinuance of the Service.
We will work carefully to provide the Service and keep it safe, secure, and free from errors. If we have worked with care, we won't be responsible for losses that aren't caused directly by our breaking these Terms or by our actions; losses that you and we couldn't have expected when we agreed to these Terms; and events beyond our control, like issues with the data or content you encounter using our video play or Classroom service, or how other people behave (online or offline).
Type of Accounts
Our Service offers two main categories of accounts: kid accounts and adult accounts. Kid accounts are further divided into three types: the free basic account; the Gold account, which requires a paid membership and provides access to premium features; and the student account, designed for use within an educational context by students at an educational institution.
Adult accounts come in three variations: Parent accounts for parents or guardians of children using the Service; Coach accounts for adults who wish to teach chess professionally; and Teacher accounts for individuals employed by schools or similar educational institutions to teach chess. The features available vary according to the type of account.
Member Accounts
At ChessKid, you can access lots of our chess-related services without needing to register. However, if you decide to register to get more access or privileges and you will need to create a username and choose a password. Remember, it's your job to keep your password and account private. You are the one responsible for any activity that happens using your account.
If someone uses your account without your permission, or if you think your account security has been breached, you need to tell us right away. Keep in mind, if your account security is compromised because you didn't keep it safe, ChessKid won't be able to help with any loss or damage that happens because of it.
You acknowledge, consent and agree that ChessKid may access, preserve and disclose your account information and Content if required to do so by law or in a good faith belief that such access preservation or disclosure is reasonably necessary to: (a) comply with legal process; (b) enforce the Terms of Service; (c) respond to claims that any Content violates the rights of third parties; (d) respond to your requests for customer service; or (e) protect the rights, property or personal safety of ChessKid, its users and the public.
Live Video Chess Play and Classroom Service
Users may have the option to participate in live video chess play in the classroom with Teachers, coaches, and/or other student users by using the Classroom feature. We do not monitor these live sessions. If you choose to use this video play and/or Classroom service, then you are responsible for the activities of all users who access the Service through your account and you agree to ensure that any such user will comply with the terms of this Agreement and all of our policies. If you become aware of any violation of this Terms of Service in connection with the use of the video play and/or Classroom service by any person, please contact
Support
. We may investigate any complaints and violations that come to our attention and may take any (or no) action that we believe is appropriate, including, but not limited to issuing warnings, removing the content, prohibiting use of the video play and/or Classroom service by an end user, or terminating an account. We also may provide user information to law enforcement and government agencies in response to valid legal requests consistent with our Privacy Policy.
If you are participating in a live streaming event (e.g. Twitch), you are not allowed to watch the live stream during your game or active gameplay session.
Ratings
On ChessKid.com, we use our own rating system consisting of a number that estimates your strength as a chess player in multiple playing methods, such as fast chess and slow chess (rapid and classical), and as a puzzle solver. This means your account will have multiple chess ratings and puzzle ratings.
Ratings on the site are independent of any official rating system. Your rating will go up and down as you win or lose games. This is the only way to calculate your rating. If you leave a fast game after our system starts the timer, regardless of making a move, your rating may go down. The amount your rating changes each time you win or lose a game depends on what your current rating is, what your opponent's rating is, and how many games each of you has completed.
It is forbidden to try to manipulate the rating of your account in an unfair way. We can detect when a user tries to manipulate their own rating in ways that go against the chess spirit and fair play.
Account Limitations
You acknowledge that ChessKid may establish rules and limits on how you can use our Service. This includes things like how long your messages or posts stay on our Service, and what features are available. You agree that ChessKid is not responsible if messages or any other content are deleted or not saved. Also, if you don't use your account for a long time, ChessKid might deactivate it. We may change these rules and limits occasionally and will notify you at least 30 days in advance, for example by email.
Termination
You agree that ChessKid suspend, disable, or delete your account and stop your access to our Service without prior notice under certain circumstances. These include (a) if, in our reasonable opinion, you have breached or violated the Terms of Service or other agreements or guidelines, (b) requests by law enforcement or other government agencies, (c) a request by you for self-initiated account deletions, (d) significant changes or discontinuation of the Service, (e) unexpected technical or security issues, (f) your involvement in fraudulent or illegal activities, and (g) failure to pay any fees owed by you in connection with the Services.
When your account is terminated in the situations detailed above, it means that (a) you will lose access to all parts of the Service, (b) your password and all related information, files, and content in your account will be deleted, and (c) you will be barred from further use of the Service. You also agree that all decisions to terminate for these reasons are up to ChessKid, and ChessKid will not be liable to you or any third party for the termination of your account or your access to the Service.
