Fair Play
ChessKid takes Fair Play seriously & the rules are the same as on our parent site Chess.com. Parents and guardians, please talk to your child(ren) about sportsmanship and fair play! Dishonest play ruins the experience for others. We want to keep the play experience fun and honest for everyone; we truly care about our users, and the integrity of chess.
ChessKid takes Fair Play abuse seriously. "Fair Play Abuse" at ChessKid means using unfair advantages to win or lose games intentionally. Our policies are clear, strict, and faithfully enforced.
We are effective in identifying and dealing with Fair Play abusers. We promptly close accounts found violating the Fair Play Policy. We will, and have closed accounts during live events as our Fair Play team monitors games in real-time. We take Fair Play very seriously and we will take actions up to and including a permanent ban from ChessKid and Chess.com.
The Fair Play Rules
No chess programs or engines
can be used to analyze positions in ongoing games at any time.
In Slow Chess (turn-based games with several days per move), you may consult any resource which is not engine-based. This includes books, opening databases (including the ChessKid Explorer) for ChessKid/openings, opening moves, and thematic games (though not their engine analyses).
Tablebases are NOT allowed. You may not consult an engine, or another human, to provide an opinion on the opening database, tablebases, self-preparation or analysis
that would relate to a particular game-in-progress on ChessKid.
In Fast Chess,
no outside assistance of any kind is permitted.
Fixing game results by
arranging games, playing with multiple accounts or losing intentionally is also against the rules.
Do not let anyone else play on your account.
If you are participating in a live streaming event (e.g. Twitch),
you are not allowed to watch the live stream during your game
or active gameplay session.
Reporting Unfair Play
If you have reason to believe someone is violating the Fair Play policies in any way like using the illegal assistance of an engine or any other conduct against the rules, please report it to support
here
. Our Fair Play Staff will
conduct a thorough
investigation, keeping all findings confidential,
taking appropriate action against the reported user if/when a concrete assessment has been made.
Please do not discuss your suspicions in the forums!
Any of the above described public accusations or public actions against a member
may lead to your own account being restricted
, regardless of what is found against the accused.
Detecting Unfair Play
Part of our analysis involves comparing human moves to computer moves and looking at the statistical significance of said moves.
To remain effective, other aspects of our detection methods are confidential.
Catching Fair Play Abusers
We work hard to keep ChessKid a safe and positive community for chess players around the world, and are sad whenever any account is closed.
That said, the process of investigating the fair play of our members is a never ending one!
We have a team dedicated to the research, prevention, and ultimately, the closure of accounts found to have accessed illegal assistance during their chess games. Our team is constantly going through the games of our top players, submitting those games into our 'Fair Play Detection System', and evaluating clean play vs non-clean play.
ChessKid continues to close accounts on a daily basis for Fair Play violations.
Players found to have violated the rules of Fair Play
Their accounts may be closed or suspended. Account closures may be permanent.
If we happen to find violations of Fair Play in real-time, we may abort the game in progress, award their opponent with a win and close their account immediately; all games in progress can be awarded to their opponents.
In many 'first time abuser' cases, we offer a chance for admission and apology. If this is given, we will at our sole discretion allow the opening of a new account or give a second chance to reopen the same account. See more details below regarding appeals.
Their rating will be reset to the original rating they had when the account was opened.
Accounts not closed after reporting abuse
We appreciate you reporting your suspicions, but ultimately ChessKid will decide if an account will be closed for abuse or not.
Can someone appeal if their account is closed or suspended?
We are happy to listen to your appeal! Reply to your closure notice and support will work with you to file an appeal.
ChessKid maintains the right to close the accounts of anyone we deem to have broken site rules or applicable laws, acted unfairly to other members or behaved in a way that hurt the site experience for other members.
